The paper deals with developing an active learning framework for mining strict partial orders, which is a common mathematical structure in relational data. This involves incorporating relational reasoning in finding new unlabeled pairs and devising new query strategies. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories such as Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Computational Linguistics (cs.CL), Databases (cs.DB), and Information Retrieval (cs.IR).
